title: Ukraine POWs Return Home In Prisoner Swap With Russia | 10 News
description: 157 Ukrainians have returned home after being imprisoned in Russia as prisoners of war, some of whom have been in captivity since 2022.  The prisoner swap came as part of peace talks between Ukraine and Russia, as the two nations look for a solution to end their conflict, which has raged for four years. title: RBA Governor Faces Parliamentary Committee Grilling Following Interest Rate Hike | 10 News
description: The Reserve Bank Governor, Michele Bullock, has dismissed Treasurer, Jim Chalmers' claims that government spending didn't contribute to Tuesday's Interest rate hike. Grilled by a committee in Canberra today, Bullock hypothesised inflation would not be under control until mid next year, meaning another hike could be on the cards. title: Bruce Highway Closure Causes Traffic Chaos After Excavator Hits Bridge On Sunshine Coast | 10 News
description: Thousands of south-east commuters are facing long delays after an excavator smashed into a bridge, raining debris on Queensland's longest road. The mid-morning crash forced the Bruce Highway to close west of Maroochydore. Tonight, it is still shut, and eight hours after the incident, there is no word on when it will reopen. title: Could Flat-Pack Homes Be The Solution To Australia's Housing Crisis? | 10 News+
description: Kit homes are emerging as a potential fix for Australia's housing crisis. title: Could Keir Starmer Be Sacked Over His US Ambassador’s Connection To Jeffrey Epstein? | 10 News+
description: UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer has apologised to Jeffrey Epstein’s victims after London police launched a criminal investigation this week into Starmer’s US Ambassador, Lord Peter Mandelson. It’s alleged that Mandelson shared sensitive information with Jeffrey Epstein in 2009 during his time as Business Minister. The PM says Lord Mandelson was asked directly about the nature of his relationship with Epstein before he was appointed as ambassador. "He portrayed Epstein as someone he barely knew,” Starmer said.
